Heat the oil in a wok until very hot. Add the prawns and stir-fry for three minutes.Add the purple sprouting broccoli, anchovies, chilli flakes and garlic and stir-fry for a further 2-3 minutes.Add the lemon juice, pak choi and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Stir-fry for 30 seconds then transfer to four serving bowls.Sprinkle each dish with sesame seeds and a little freshly grated nutmeg and serve.